verses.rendering:
For a tree has hope:
if it is cut down, it will sprout again,
and its new shoots will not stop coming.

so a man lies down and does not rise.
Until the heavens are no more, they will not awake;
they will not be roused from their sleep.

Water wears away stones;
floods wash away the soil of the earth —
and so you destroy the hope of a mortal.
